properties.areaDesc: Coastal waters from Cape Shoalwater WA to Cascade Head OR out 10 nm; Waters from Cape Shoalwater WA to Cascade Head OR from 10 to 60 nm
properties.headline: Gale Watch issued January 6 at 3:03AM PST until January 7 at 4:00PM PST by NWS Portland OR
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Gale Warning, southwest winds 25 to 30 kt with
gusts up to 35 kt and seas 13 to 17 feet at 12 seconds. For
the Gale Watch, south winds 25 to 30 kt with gusts up to 35 kt
and seas 11 to 15 feet at 12 seconds possible.

* WHERE...Coastal waters from Cape Shoalwater WA to Cascade Head
OR out 10 NM and Waters from Cape Shoalwater WA to Cascade
Head OR from 10 to 60 NM.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, until 4 PM PST this afternoon.
For the Gale Watch, from late tonight through Tuesday
afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 PM PST THIS AFTERNOON... ...GALE WATCH IN EFFECT FROM LATE TONIGHT THROUGH TUESDAY AFTERNOON
